Shipping quick. As another reviewer mentioned, not sure exactly of the contents of these capsules and was confused by the herbal filler. Took them with my partner last night- definitely opiate but we weren't sure they were typical of a Norcos high.

OK...so I've eaten A LOT of Hydrocodone in my day. It is my recreational drug of choice, so I'm very familiar with the substance and exactly how it makes me feel and what to expect when I take it.

That being said, these mysterious clear capsules definitely have Hydrocodone in them...but, they're somehow different than the Watsons/Norcos I've taken countless times before.

They also have a different taste, the powder is an off white/dirty white looking color and they smell as if some kind of herbal supplement was added. I'd really like to know exactly how these capsules are made and if there is any other additive in them.

I'm guessing these are hand encapsulated, so that could explain the inconsistency. They're potent once they kick in, but don't seem to last as long as the pressed, brand name tabs I'm used to. I guess that's expected since they're in encapsulated form and thus deliver quickly once the capsule is digested.

The price is good for what you get, but not sure if I"ll give them another try as I still prefer a brand name 10mg tablet to these mysterious 15mg capsules.

Your mileage my vary though...they're certainly worth a try for the price.

I'm guessing these are hand encapsulated, so that could explain the inconsistency. They're potent once they kick in, but don't seem to last as long as the pressed, brand name tabs I'm used to. I guess that's expected since they're in encapsulated form and thus deliver quickly once the capsule is digested.

The price is good for what you get, but not sure if I"ll give them another try as I still prefer a brand name 10mg tablet to these mysterious 15mg capsules.

Your mileage my vary though...they're certainly worth a try for the price.

OK...so I've eaten A LOT of Hydrocodone in my day. It is my recreational drug of choice, so I'm very familiar with the substance and exactly how it makes me feel and what to expect when I take it.

That being said, these mysterious clear capsules definitely have Hydrocodone in them...but, they're somehow different than the Watsons/Norcos I've taken countless times before.

They also have a different taste, the powder is an off white/dirty white looking color and they smell as if some kind of herbal supplement was added. I'd really like to know exactly how these capsules are made and if there is any other additive in them.

I'm guessing these are hand encapsulated, so that could explain the inconsistency. They're potent once they kick in, but don't seem to last as long as the pressed, brand name tabs I'm used to. I guess that's expected since they're in encapsulated form and thus deliver quickly once the capsule is digested.

The price is good for what you get, but not sure if I"ll give them another try as I still prefer a brand name 10mg tablet to these mysterious 15mg capsules.

Your mileage my vary though...they're certainly worth a try for the price.
